Description: 2008 limited edition FSR American Select deluxe stratocaster. In great condition. One apparent nick/ding(pictured). Normal players wear, everything works as it should. This guitar is set up with 10s. Comes with SKB molded hardshell case. Glad to answer any questions. Special edition delivers a hot humbucker at the bridge and a mahogany body. This mahogany Fender American Select Stratocaster HSS guitar features 3 incredible-sounding Fender pickups: a Diamondback humbucker and two custom-staggered Tex-Mex single-coils. With the original Strat guitar body shape and tremolo bridge, this is a Stratocaster that rocks with a traditional vibe and screams out modern sonics with the hot humbucker at the bridge. The American Select Strat has a fast, modern C-shape maple neck with rolled edges on the fretboard and 22 medium-jumbo frets. Crimson red transparent finish looks killer and highlights the mahogany wood grain. FEATURES--- Big Muff with tone wicker Mahogany body Modern C-shape maple neck 9.5" radius rosewood fingerboard 22 medium-jumbo frets Rolled-edge fretboard 2 custom-staggered Tex-Mex single-coil pickups (neck and middle) Diamondback humbucker (bridge) 5-way pickup switching Fender S1 switching located on the volume knob American 2-point synchronized tremolo with stainless steel saddles Fender Deluxe staggered cast/sealed tuners Chrome hardware Abalone dot inlays Comfort carved heel joint 25.5" scale LSR Roller Nut at 1.6875" nut width SKB molded case Straplocks This is one sweet axe that stands out from the crowd. Great playing, awesome sounding strat, she will be missed.
Title: Fender American Deluxe stratocaster FSR Mahogany body Limited Edition
